eNCA’s Siphokazi Malinga caught up with Usuthu ahead of matchday five in the group stage. #DStv403 DURBAN - AmaZulu’s continental pedigree will be tested once again when Raja Casablanca confront them at the Moses Mabhida Stadium. A win will keep Usuthu among the frontrunners in Group B of the Caf Champions League. Despite losing two of their four group games, Usuthu know that a win against Morocco’s Raja Casablanca would be a big step in their quest to make the quarter-finals. * eNCA’s Siphokazi Malinga reports.